This paper deals with wireless caching and device to device communication in a cellular network, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization problems and algorithms for delay minimization, which could be categorized under information theory (cs.IT) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of caching for popular files and video content popularity analysis could also be related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM).
